Even though we removed border-radius globally, Grid toolbar buttons sometimes inherit radius from .k-button-icontext or theme base styles.

We’ll target that button specifically and force it to be square with black border.

✅ Append This at Bottom of Vehicle-Estimate.css
/* =========================================================
   FIX: Add New Vehicle Estimate Button (Grid Toolbar)
   ========================================================= */

/* Target toolbar button specifically */
#VehicleGrid .k-grid-toolbar .k-button,
#VehicleGrid .k-grid-toolbar .k-button-icontext {
    border-radius: 0 !important;      /* remove rounded corners */
    background: white !important;     /* white background */
    color: black !important;          /* black text */
    border: 1px solid black !important; /* solid black border */
    box-shadow: none !important;      /* remove shadow */
}

/* Hover */
#VehicleGrid .k-grid-toolbar .k-button:hover {
    background: #f2f2f2 !important;
    border-color: black !important;
}
✅ If It Is STILL Rounded

Inspect the button.
If you see class:

k-rounded-md
k-rounded-lg

Then add this also:

.k-rounded-md,
.k-rounded-lg,
.k-rounded-full {
    border-radius: 0 !important;
}

(Newer Telerik themes use these utility classes.)

